Super Eagles attacker Samuel Kalu was officially unveiled as a player for English Premier League strugglers Watford yesterday. The Hornets have confirmed the signing of the 24-year-old on a three-and-a-half-year deal from Ligue 1 club Bordeaux and with the transfer fee in the region of £2.5-£3.5 million. Kalu completed his medical on Wednesday ahead of his move to the Premier League side.   Aribo: Rangers legend prayed for Eagles’ AFCON crash     Eagles ‘ll bounce back after AFCON disappointment, says Musa     Mouktar wants Qatar 2022 Task Force for Eagles   It is understood that Watford have been tracking Kalu for a number of years and made the decision to move this month. Kalu joined Watford a day after Roy Hodgson was appointed as their new manager, following Claudio Ranieri’s dismissal after three and a half months into the role. - Advertisement - The winger recently asked for permission to be left out of the national team setup in a bid to concentrate on his club career.